{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan an Nasai","section":{"9":{"eng-name":"The Book of the Qiblah","ara-name":"كتاب القبلة"}},"section_detail":{"9":{"hadithnumber_first":742,"hadithnumber_last":776,"arabicnumber_first":742,"arabicnumber_last":776}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":772,"arabicnumber":772,"text":"It was narrated from Awn bin Abi Juhaifah, from his father that, the Messenger of Allah(ﷺ) went out in a red Hullah, and he set up a short spear (Anazah) and prayed facing toward it, while dogs, women and donkeys were passing beyond it","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Muslim"}],"reference":{"book":9,"hadith":31},"chapter":{"id":21,"ara-name":"باب الصَّلاَةِ فِي الثِّيَابِ الْحُمُرِ","eng-name":"Praying in red garments","isFirstHadith":true}}]}